This paper deals with the design and analysis of Application-Level FEC codes for the Packet Erasure Channel, which is a topic related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the encoding and decoding complexity of the codes, which is a topic related to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a new coding technique that bridges the gap between block and convolutional codes, which is a topic related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
